In sum, the Classic Rock/AOR CD matches my stated priorities (vocal‑forward, punchy, hook‑driven, dynamic preservation, tasteful coloration), whereas Hybrid Theory, despite being hooky and energetic, conflicts with my dislikes around heavy distortion, compressed loudness and a production aesthetic that can overshadow the kind of intimate‑but‑energetic lead vocals and natural timbres I favor.

